ar.org/paper/b3e268e404c45e4b90e0839f9c3963c5fe2fd320\n09 | score=None | year=2025 | Do Large Language Models Exhibit Spontaneous Rational Deception?\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/38460cd7d1006a55439a288de10df76fef81dd44\n10 | score=None | year=2024 | Language Models can Subtly Deceive Without Lying: A Case Study on Strategic Phrasing in Legislation\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/1342bea993d3d962ca1ad4241ce403a9c3fddf45\n11 | score=None | year=2024 | Redefining \"Hallucination\" in LLMs: Towards a psychology-informed framework for mitigating misinformation\n    https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusId:267412055\n12 | score=None | year=2024 | AI-LieDar: Examine the Trade-off Between Utility and Truthfulness in LLM Agents\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/2cba552e717dbe4a97669737e1b9653fa1880703\n13 | score=None | year=2023 | Alignment for Honesty\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/6cfbbf7604adda1df65932e3c4d157770a2df000\n14 | score=None | year=2026 | Lying to Win: Assessing LLM Deception through Human-AI Games and Parallel-World Probing\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/7fc7f62e2e690672ede2271b7a7a8ad06e53503d\n15 | score=None | year=2026 | Distortion Instead of Hallucination: The Effect of Reasoning Under Strict Constraints\n    https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusId:284488763\n16 | score=None | year=2025 | DeceptionBench: A Comprehensive Benchmark for AI Deception Behaviors in Real-world Scenarios\n    https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusId:282203674\n17 | score=None | year=2023 | Large Language Models can Strategically Deceive their Users when Put Under Pressure\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/50ac089843f685e73d43f083a27109b91a4dec1c\n18 | score=None | year=2025 | LLMs Deceive Unintentionally: Emergent Misalignment in Dishonesty from Misaligned Samples to Biased Human-AI Interactions\n    https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/2d2c452d5408abfd420d16047950557363be1953\n19 | score=None | year=2026 | N